    <etym xml:lang="ru">Сложение %iæm-tæf%i = <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                ><lang/><w>*ham-tapah-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>sāṃ-tapas-</w><gloss><q>жар</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*antap-(ʽntp)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                ><lang/><w>andaw</w><gloss><q>жар</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘лихорадка’, <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/><w>antāpce</w><gloss><q>пожар</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Windokens"/><biblScope>5</biblScope></bibl>W i n d е k е n
        s 5). <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>tæf</w></mentioned> (=<mentioned
            xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>tapah-</w></mentioned>) существует и самостоятельно в
        значении ‘пар’, ‘дух’, ‘запах’. Кроме того, древнеиранскую основу %itap%i- ‘греть’, ‘топить’
        и пр. мы находим в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tavyn"/> ‘греть’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ændavyn"/> id., <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsyn"/> ‘согреваться’,
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsæg"/> ‘лихорадка’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tævd"
        /> ‘горячий’; см. эти слова.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>32</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The composition %iæm-tæy%i relates to <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                ><lang/><w>*ham-tapah-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>sāṃ-tapas-</w><gloss><q>heat</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*antap-(ʽntp)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                ><lang/><w>andaw</w><gloss><q>heat</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘fever’, <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/><w>antāpce</w><gloss><q>fire</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Windokens"/><biblScope>5</biblScope></bibl>). <mentioned
            xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>tæf</w></mentioned> (=<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                ><lang/><w>tapah-</w></mentioned>) is found in language with the meaning ‘steam’,
        ‘spirit (breath?)’, ‘smell’. Besides that, old Iranian stem %itap%i- ‘to warm’, ‘to melt’
        and so on is found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tavyn"/> ‘to warm’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ændavyn"/> id., <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsyn"/> ‘to warm
        oneself’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsæg"/> ‘fever’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_tævd"/> ‘hot’; see these words.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>32</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
